To me, it&#39;s a net positive to have VOs run their own services.  Even though there is some overlap with the OSG Singularity repo, I view this as a step toward exploring in-housing some of the OSG / LIGO integrations.

As you know, we&#39;ve been working to overhaul the singularity / docker / CVMFS integration to use more standardized libraries (e.g., docker-py instead of internal Singularity code).  This has now landed, meaning we have some chance to actually share code.  Particularly, I&#39;d be excited to figure out why your scripts are working well with authenticated instances and ours aren&#39;t.  I&#39;d also be curious about landing some webhooks&#58; even though we synchronize O(50) times a day, there&#39;s still a significant difference between that and a push-based update.

Outside this ticket - would it be possible to either&#58;
a) Setup a chat with you, me, Dave, and Derek on the best way to move forward.
b) Have you present your work at the next global CVMFS coordination meeting?

Thanks!

Brian

