Further context&#58; I am setting up a LIGO-specific service similar to singularity.opensciencegrid.org aimed to storing container images produced by our researchers. My understanding is that you want a repo whose name ends in *.opensciencegrid.org (rather than, say, binaries.ligo.org). I do expect that will mean that the containers currently stored under /cvmfs/singularity.opensciencegrid.org/{ligo,pycbc} will migrate to this namespace. I do not presently have a timescale for it since I don&#39;t know the real difficulties of maintaining a CVMSF repo. But that is the goal.

